      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "There are in fact many things that can break when upgrading a java version. It&#39;s less critical for a back-end application which runs on a big server, but it does matter for client applications. The graphical libraries and garbage collection strategies are impacted often by major and minor java upgrades. On top of that, client software can run on various operating systems and sometimes with limited memory, which means you often won&#39;t have the budget/resources to test everything. - Yes, I have customers that still stick with Java 5 in 2017."
