  "title" : "Should I use string.isEmpty() or &quot;&quot;.equals(string)?",
  "body" : "<p>I'm usually testing this alongside a <code>string == null</code>, so I'm not really concerned about a null-safe test. Which should I use?</p>\n<pre><code>String s = /* whatever */;\n...\nif (s == null || &quot;&quot;.equals(s))\n{\n    // handle some edge case here\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>or</p>\n<pre><code>if (s == null || s.isEmpty())\n{\n    // handle some edge case here\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>On that note - does <code>isEmpty()</code> even do anything other than <code>return this.equals(&quot;&quot;);</code> or <code>return this.length() == 0;</code>?</p>\n"
